{"branch":"main","confidence":85,"prompt":"Backpressure-based adaptive system:

MECHANISM:
- Each worker reports load metrics via existing RPC
- Central coordinator (main thread or dedicated worker) tracks system load
- When recording starts: coordinator tells playback workers to reduce work
- Playback workers adapt: skip frames, reduce buffer size, lower decode quality

ADAPTIVE STRATEGIES:
1. Frame skipping: Only decode keyframes during recording
2. Buffer reduction: 30 frames → 5 frames during recording
3. Quality reduction: Request lower resolution decode if codec supports
4. Temporal decimation: Decode every 2nd frame, interpolate visually

PROS:
- Uses existing RPC infrastructure
- Graceful degradation
- No SharedArrayBuffer requirements
- Easy to tune thresholds

CONS:
- Slightly higher latency (async messages)
- Coordination logic on main thread
- Need to implement in each worker

IMPLEMENTATION SKETCH:
```ts
// Coordinator
function onRecordingStart() {
  for (const worker of playbackWorkers) {
    worker.setMode('low-priority')
  }
}

// Playback worker
setMode(mode: 'normal' | 'low-priority') {
  if (mode === 'low-priority') {
    BUFFER_MAX_FRAMES = 5
    skipNonKeyframes = true
  }
}
```"}
